                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 511.4Al/1514a.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Minister <persName type="to">Van Dyke</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-09-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 23, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>200. Ascertain and cable what countries have deposited with Netherlands
                    Government their ratifications of International Opium Convention in accordance
                    with protocol of Second Conference, and what is prospect of deposit of
                    ratifications by other governments; also whether there is any likelihood of any
                    of the governments who have deposited ratifications effectuating the convention
                    as have the United States, China, and the Netherlands.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
